raw:
American mathematician
Jekuthiel Ginsburg (1889–1957) was a professor of mathematics at Yeshiva University. He established the journal Scripta Mathematica. He also was honored as a fellow of the New York Academy of Sciences.

References[edit]
Boyer, Carl B. (1958), "Jekuthiel Ginsburg (1889–1957)", Isis, The History of Science Society, 49 (3): 335–336, doi:10.1086/348677, JSTOR 226941.
Furstenberg, Hillel (Harry) (May 16, 2005), "Inspiring the Love of Mathematics: The Legacy of Jekuthiel Ginsburg at Yeshiva", The Commentator.
